Title: Carotid traumatic aneurysm treated by detachable balloon.
Abstract: The authors report the case of a young man who developed a large infraclinoid carotid aneurysm following a blunt head injury and presented with epistaxis. The aneurysm was occluded by a detachable balloon resulting in a good recovery.
