Title: Down's syndrome with hydrocephalus treated by compressive head binding.
Abstract: A child with Down's syndrome, hydrocephalus and porencephaly is described, and treatment by compressive head binding is discussed. Although binding did not stop enlargement of the head it did achieve a reduction in the rate of enlargement.
