Title: Bilateral osteochondritis dissecans of the elbow treated by Herbert screw fixation.
Abstract: The case of a 15-year-old boy, a high-performance motocross rider, who developed bilateral osteochondritis dissecans of the elbow is described. Both lesions were successfully treated by Herbert screw internal fixation.
